
[1]piety

   PI'ETY, n. [L. pietas, from pius, or its root, probably a contracted
   word.]

   1. Piety in principle, is a compound of veneration or reverence of the
   Supreme Being and love of his character, or veneration accompanied with
   love; and piety in practice, is

   the exercise of these affections in obedience to his will and devotion
                               to his service.

   Piety is the only proper and adequate relief of decaying man.

   2. Reverence of parents or friends, accompanied with affection and
   devotion to their honor and happiness.
